":"1302","1357":"1357","1300":"1300","1267":"1267","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","1386":"1386","1298":"1298","Kirkton of Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Schotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Scotland":"Dundee, Forfarshire, Schotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Skottland":"Dundee, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1300–1341":"1300–1341","1292–1357":"1292–1357","1298–1365":"1298–1365","1302–1338":"1302–1338","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1332–Female":"1332–Deceased","1267–1350":"1267–1350","1267–Female":"1267–Deceased","9 January 1338":"9 January 1338","1341":"1341","1350":"1350","1292":"1292","1338":"1338","1324":"1324","1302":"1302","1357":"1357","1300":"1300","1267":"1267","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","1386":"1386","1298":"1298","Kirkton of Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Scotland":"Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Skottland":"Dundee, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ramsay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and English: variant (the usual spelling in Scotland) of   Ramsey  . The Scottish Ramsays derive from Simund <i>de Ramesie</i>, recorded before 1175, who went to Scotland from Ramsey (Huntingdonshire)."],"variants":[{"name":"Ramsey","meanings":["Scottish, English, and Irish (Antrim): habitational name from Ramsey (Huntingdonshire, now part of Cambridgeshire), from Old English <i>hramsa</i> ‘wild garlic’ + <i>ēg</i> ‘island, low-lying land’. Alternatively, the name may also arise from Ramsey (Essex), probably from the same etymology as the Huntingdonshire placename. However, this is unlikely to be the source of the Scottish surname. This form of the surname is also common in Ireland, where it is probably in most if not all cases an altered form of Scottish   Ramsay  ."]}]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Ramsay was born in 1300, in Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland, his father, Robert Ramsay - First Laird of Auchterhouse, was 33 and his mother, Lady Ramsay, was 34. He married Ella House. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1341, in Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1300–1341":"1300–1341","1292–1357":"1292–1357","1298–1365":"1298–1365","1302–1338":"1302–1338","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1332–Female":"1332–Surnud","1267–1350":"1267–1350","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","9 January 1338":"9. jaanuar 1338","1341":"1341","1350":"1350","1292":"1292","1338":"1338","1324":"1324","1302":"1302","1357":"1357","1300":"1300","1267":"1267","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","1386":"1386","1298":"1298","Kirkton of Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Scotland":"Dundee, Forfarshire, Scotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Skottland":"Dundee, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1300–1341":"1300–1341","1292–1357":"1292–1357","1298–1365":"1298–1365","1302–1338":"1302–1338","1324–1386":"1324–1386","1332–Female":"1332–Kuollut","1267–1350":"1267–1350","1267–Female":"1267–Kuollut","9 January 1338":"9. tammikuuta 1338","1341":"1341","1350":"1350","1292":"1292","1338":"1338","1324":"1324","1302":"1302","1357":"1357","1300":"1300","1267":"1267","1332":"1332","1365":"1365","138